Timid Tadano is a total wallflower, and thats just the way he likes it. But all that changes when he finds himself alone in a classroom on the first day of high school with the legendary Komi. He quickly realizes she isnt aloofshes just super awkward. Now hes made it his mission to help her on her quest to make 100 friends!
(Source: Viz Media)

A boy fights... for "the right death." Hardship, regret, shame: the negative feelings that humans feel become Curses that lurk in our everyday lives. The Curses run rampant throughout the world, capable of leading people to terrible misfortune and even death. What's more, the Curses can only be exorcised by another Curse. Itadori Yuji is a boy with tremendous physical strength, though he lives a completely ordinary high school life. One day, to save a friend who has been attacked by Curses, he eats the finger of the Double-Faced Specter, taking the Curse into his own soul. From then on, he shares one body with the Double-Faced Specter. Guided by the most powerful of sorcerers, Gojou Satoru, Itadori is admitted to the Tokyo Metropolitan Technical High School of Sorcery, an organization that fights the Curses... and thus begins the heroic tale of a boy who became a Curse to exorcise a Curse, a life from which he could never turn back. (Source: Crunchyroll) Note: The first episode received an early web premiere on September 19th, 2020. The regular TV broadcast started on October 3rd, 2020.
Takane-san, Kimi no Koto Sukirashii yo

"I heard that Takamine-san likes you."
The head of the school discipline committee, Kengo Mashima, heard a rumor from an unknown source...... It turned out that the source was none other than Takamine-san herself, who wanted Mashima-kun to show more interest in her! But the overly serious Mashima-kun didn't get the hint: ......
"Saki Takamine, I heard you have a crush on me?"
"Why are you asking me for? ......!"
Actually, Mashima-kun liked Takamine-san, too. The first time you see these two, you'll be writhing in frustration at their innocent denseness!
(Source: Gagaga Bunko, translated)
Ao no Outline: Tensai no Egaku Sekai wo Bonjin ga Nurikaeru Houhou

"Fascinating" "Overwhelming" "Addictive" "Captivating"
Those are the reactions when people see her paintings.
As a high school student and aspiring artist, I desperately wanted to paint like her.
Yuri Kashiwazaki, the girl who is regarded a "genius," no matter what she draws.

"I just came by to see you. I only paint when I want to."

She is my childhood friend, at once the closest and furthest person to me. One day, she just stopped painting, but I remained in her shadow and continued to wield my paintbrush.

"I'm going to keep painting. I won't give up. I won't use talent as an excuse."

Until the day when Yuri starts painting again. Until the day she will admire my paintings.

This is the story of an ordinary boy who devotes his youth to art, to challenge a "genius."

(Source: Fantasia Bunko, translated)
